rProvider</code> and use the <code>useProver()</code> hook</li>\\n<li>Call <code>waitAndEmbedProof()</code> to generate and embed the proof, or use <code>requestProof()</code> + <code>useProofRequestStatus()</code> for progress tracking</li>\\n</ul>\\n</li>\\n<li><strong>Upload</strong>: Upload the verifiable zPhoto to the news platform&#x27;s backend for use in articles</li>\\n</ol>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/overview/example_usecases.mdx#mobile-camera-app-integration\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nSteps for the reporter app:\\n\\nInstallation: Follow the Installation guide to set up the SDK\\nCamera Setup: Use react-native-zcam1-capture to initialize the camera:\\n\\nCall initCapture() to initialize device keys and attestation\\nUse the `` component to render the camera preview\\nCall takePhoto() to capture a zPhoto with verifiable bindings\\n\\n\\nProof Generation (Optional): Use react-native-zcam1-prove to generate zero-knowledge proofs:\\n\\nWrap your app with ProverProvider and use the useProver() hook\\nCall waitAndEmbedProof() to generate and embed the proof, or use requestProof() + useProofRequestStatus() for progress tracking\\n\\n\\nUpload: Upload the verifiable zPhoto to the news platform&#x27;s backend for use in articles\\n\\n\",\"title\":\"Mobile Camera App Integration\",\"titles\":[\"Example Use Cases\",\"Verifiable News Platform\"]},{\"href\":\"/overview/example_usecases#web-platform-integration\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>On the news platform&#x27;s website, articles display verifiable zPhotos with verification controls:</p>\\n<ol>\\n<li><strong>Photo Display</strong>: Embedded zPhotos include C2PA content credentials\\n<ul>\\n<li>Users with C2PA browser extensions can view content credentials</li>\\n<li>The platform can show verification status badges</li>\\n</ul>\\n</li>\\n<li><strong>Client-Side Verification</strong>: Integrate <code>react-native-zcam1-verify</code> (or web equivalent):\\n<ul>\\n<li>Add a &quot;Verify&quot; button for each zPhoto</li>\\n<li>Call <code>verifyHash()</code> and <code>verifyProof()</code> to validate authenticity</li>\\n<li>Display verification results (e.g., &quot;✓ Verified Authentic&quot;)</li>\\n</ul>\\n</li>\\n<li><strong>Metadata Display</strong>: Surface fields from the C2PA manifest:\\n<ul>\\n<li>Capture timestamp, device information, app identifier</li>\\n<li>Allow readers to inspect the verification chain</li>\\n</ul>\\n</li>\\n</ol>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/overview/example_usecases.mdx#web-platform-integration\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nOn the news platform&#x27;s website, articles display verifiable zPhotos with verification controls:\\n\\nPhoto Display: Embedded zPhotos include C2PA content credentials\\n\\nUsers with C2PA browser extensions can view content credentials\\nThe platform can show verification status badges\\n\\n\\nClient-Side Verification: Integrate react-native-zcam1-verify (or web equivalent):\\n\\nAdd a &quot;Verify&quot; button for each zPhoto\\nCall verifyHash() and verifyProof() to validate authenticity\\nDisplay verification results (e.g., &quot;✓ Verified Authentic&quot;)\\n\\n\\nMetadata Display: Surface fields from the C2PA manifest:\\n\\nCapture timestamp, device information, app identifier\\nAllow readers to inspect the verification chain\\n\\n\\n\\n\",\"title\":\"Web Platform Integration\",\"titles\":[\"Example Use Cases\",\"Verifiable News Platform\"]},{\"href\":\"/overview/example_usecases#car-insurance-claim-app\",\"html\":\"\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/overview/example_usecases.mdx#car-insurance-claim-app\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\n\",\"title\":\"Car Insurance Claim App\",\"titles\":[\"Example Use Cases\"]},{\"href\":\"/overview/example_usecases#use-case-overview-1\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>Insurance companies often accept photos submitted via mobile apps. That has increased incentive for AI editing scams where claimants manipulate images to fraudulently file claims. The ZCAM SDK ensures zPhotos uploaded for claims were taken on an iPhone using the insurer&#x27;s app and have not been altered since capture.</p>\\n<p><strong>What We&#x27;re Building:</strong> An automated fraud detection system integrated into the claims workflow:</p>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Camera functionality inside the insurer&#x27;s mobile app using the ZCAM SDK</li>\\n<li>A backend verification service that automatically validates submitted zPhotos</li>\\n<li>An automated triage system that flags suspicious claims based on verification and metadata analysis</li>\\n</ul>\\n<strong>Value of Verifiable zPhotos:</strong>\\n<ul>\\n<li><strong>Fraud Prevention</strong>: Automatically detect and reject claims with manipulated or inauthentic zPhotos</li>\\n<li><strong>Cost Reduction</strong>: Reduce manual review by automating verification and escalating only suspicious cases</li>\\n</ul>\\n<p><strong>Verification Pattern:</strong> Internal verification — the insurer verifies zPhotos as part of backend claim processing.</p>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/overview/example_usecases.mdx#use-case-overview-1\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nInsurance companies often accept photos submitted via mobile apps. That has increased incentive for AI editing scams where claimants manipulate images to fraudulently file claims. The ZCAM SDK ensures zPhotos uploaded for claims were taken on an iPhone using the insurer&#x27;s app and have not been altered since capture.\\nWhat We&#x27;re Building: An automated fraud detection system integrated into the claims workflow:\\n\\nCamera functionality inside the insurer&#x27;s mobile app using the ZCAM SDK\\nA backend verification service that automatically validates submitted zPhotos\\nAn automated triage system that flags suspicious claims based on verification and metadata analysis\\n\\nValue of Verifiable zPhotos:\\n\\nFraud Prevention: Automatically detect and reject claims with manipulated or inauthentic zPhotos\\nCost Reduction: Reduce manual review by automating verification and escalating only suspicious cases\\n\\nVerification Pattern: Internal verification — the insurer verifies zPhotos as part of backend claim processing.\\n\",\"title\":\"Use Case Overview\",\"titles\":[\"Example Use Cases\",\"Car Insurance Claim App\"]},{\"href\":\"/overview/example_usecases#integration-architecture-1\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>The insurer integrates the ZCAM SDK in two places:</p>\\n<ol>\\n<li><strong>Mobile App</strong> (for policyholders): Integration into the claim filing flow</li>\\n<li><strong>Backend Claim Processing</strong>: Automated verification during claim triage</li>\\n</ol>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/overview/example_usecases.mdx#integration-architecture-1\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nThe insurer integrates the ZCAM SDK in two places:\\n\\nMobile App (for policyholders): Integration into the claim filing flow\\nBackend Claim Processing: Automated verification during claim triage\\n\\n\",\"title\":\"Integration Architecture\",\"titles\":[\"Example Use Cases\",\"Car Insurance Claim App\"]},{\"href\":\"/overview/example_usecases#mobile-app-integration\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>The ZCAM SDK is integrated into the claim filing flow:</p>\\n<ol>\\n<li><strong>Installation</strong>: Follow the <a href=\\\"/getting-started/installation\\\">Installation guide</a></li>\\n<li><strong>Camera Integration</strong>: Inject the `` component where users photograph their vehicle:\\n<ul>\\n<li>The SDK provides camera preview functionality</li>\\n<li>Call <code>takePhoto()</code> to capture a verifiable zPhoto</li>\\n</ul>\\n</li>\\n<li><strong>Proof Generation</strong> (Optional): Use <code>react-native-zcam1-prove</code> to attach zero-knowledge proofs:\\n<ul>\\n<li>Use <code>waitAndEmbedProof()</code> to generate and embed proofs</li>\\n</ul>\\n</li>\\n<li><strong>Claim Submission</strong>: Attach verifiable zPhotos to the claim and upload to the backend</li>\\n</ol>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/overview/example_usecases.mdx#mobile-app-integration\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nThe ZCAM SDK is integrated into the claim filing flow:\\n\\nInstallation: Follow the Installation guide\\nCamera Integration: Inject the `` component where users photograph their vehicle:\\n\\nThe SDK provides camera preview functionality\\nCall takePhoto() to capture a verifiable zPhoto\\n\\n\\nProof Generation (Optional): Use react-native-zcam1-prove to attach zero-knowledge proofs:\\n\\nUse waitAndEmbedProof() to generate and embed proofs\\n\\n\\nClaim Submission: Attach verifiable zPhotos to the claim and upload to the backend\\n\\n\",\"title\":\"Mobile App Integration\",\"titles\":[\"Example Use Cases\",\"Car Insurance Claim App\"]},{\"href\":\"/overview/example_usecases#backend-claim-processing-integration\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>On the backend, verification is part of claim triage:</p>\\n<ol>\\n<li><strong>Automated Verification</strong>: Automatically verify all attached zPhotos:\\n<ul>\\n<li>Integrate <code>react-native-zcam1-verify</code> (or server-side equivalent)</li>\\n<li>For each zPhoto, call <code>verifyHash()</code> and <code>verifyProof()</code></li>\\n<li>Confirm the zPhoto was taken using the insurer&#x27;s app</li>\\n</ul>\\n</li>\\n<li><strong>Metadata Analysis</strong>: Use C2PA fields to validate the claim:\\n<ul>\\n<li>Verify location matches the claim</li>\\n<li>Check timestamp aligns with the incident time</li>\\n<li>Validate device and app identifiers</li>\\n</ul>\\n</li>\\n<li><strong>Claim Decision</strong>: Based on verification:\\n<ul>\\n<li><strong>Verification passes</strong>: Proceed with normal processing</li>\\n<li><strong>Verification fails</strong>: Flag for manual review or deny</li>\\n</ul>\\n</li>\\n</ol>\\n<p><strong>Result</strong>: Insurers can automatically detect fraudulent claims with manipulated zPhotos, reducing fraud and processing costs while preserving a smooth experience for legitimate claimants.</p>\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/overview/example_usecases.mdx#backend-claim-processing-integration\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nOn the backend, verification is part of claim triage:\\n\\nAutomated Verification: Automatically verify all attached zPhotos:\\n\\nIntegrate react-native-zcam1-verify (or server-side equivalent)\\nFor each zPhoto, call verifyHash() and verifyProof()\\nConfirm the zPhoto was taken using the insurer&#x27;s app\\n\\n\\nMetadata Analysis: Use C2PA fields to validate the claim:\\n\\nVerify location matches the claim\\nCheck timestamp aligns with the incident time\\nValidate device and app identifiers\\n\\n\\nClaim Decision: Based on verification:\\n\\nVerification passes: Proceed with normal processing\\nVerification fails: Flag for manual review or deny\\n\\n\\n\\nResult: Insurers can automatically detect fraudulent claims with manipulated zPhotos, reducing fraud and processing costs while preserving a smooth experience for legitimate claimants.\",\"title\":\"Backend Claim Processing Integration\",\"titles\":[\"Example Use Cases\",\"Car Insurance Claim App\"]}]}}"
